{"lemma":"طُوفانُ","slug":"طُوفانُ","root":"ط.#.ف","root_slug":"ط-_-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-_-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"طُوفان","root":"طوف","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27315"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%8F%D9%88%D9%81%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"storm"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"deluge"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"inundation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"typhoon"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Through Aramaic ܛܘܦܢܐ / טוֹפָנָא (ṭōpānā) (Classical Syriac ܛܲܘܦܵܢܵܐ (ṭawpānā)), probably from a Sinitic language, though it has also been suggested that the term could be natively Semitic: see typhoon for more. Compare Cantonese 大風 /大风 (daai⁶ fung¹, “big wind”) and Ancient Greek τυφῶν (tuphôn)."},"ipa":["/tˤuː.faːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27315","headword_ar":"طُوفَانٌ","root":"Twf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An overpowering rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overpowering water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a meaning erroneously assigned in the CK to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taw~aAf","text_ar":"طَوَّاف"},{"kind":"text","text":"instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwfaAn","text_ar":"طُوفَان"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that covers"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overwhelms"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"everything;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA;) in the common conventional acceptation,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water abounding to the utmost degree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a flood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deluge;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] such as befell the people of Noah; (TA;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwfaAnu AlmaA='i","text_ar":"طُوفَانُ المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the water that covers"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overwhelms"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"everything:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a drowning torrent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything, [like as we say"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a flood"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as includes the generality of persons,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"things, within its compass:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) and particularly (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"death;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick and wide-spreading, death;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"death commonly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generally, prevailing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick and wide-spreading, death, commonly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generally, prevailing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and extensive"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slaughter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any accident"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil accident"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that besets a man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trial,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affliction:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and El-'Ajjáj likens to the rain, or water, thus called, the darkness of night; using the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwfaAnu AlZ~alaAmi","text_ar":"طُوفَانُ الظَّلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Kh, S;) by which he means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the intensity of the darkness"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the night: (TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwfaAnN","text_ar":"طُوفَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to be a pl. [or coll. gen. n.]; (Msb, TA;) and its sing. [or n. un.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwfaAnapN","text_ar":"طُوفَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K, TA,) accord. to analogy: (S:) thus says Akh: (S, TA:) or it is an inf. n., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujoHaAnN","text_ar":"رُجْحَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuqoSaAnN","text_ar":"نُقْصَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAfa","text_ar":"طَافَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaTuwfu","text_ar":"يَطُوفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, TA:) thus says Abu-l- 'Abbás; and he says that there is no need of seeking for it a sing.: some say that it is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuloEaAnN","text_ar":"فُلْعَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TafaA AlmaA='u","text_ar":"طَفَا المَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaTofuw","text_ar":"يَطْفُو"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning “ the water rose, ” or “ became high; ” the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"being transposed to the place of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E","text_ar":"ع"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but this is strange. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","TA","S"]}]}}